as was mother's great - day, we had a - always had a wonderful Christmas. And every year - they made this vow when they got married that every Christmas Day they would invite some lonely person to join the family circle, and they - continued that the whol
e
 of their lives. They always had somebody. At one time it was a - for several years an old - widow, poor hard up widow called Mrs Malcolm, came, we used to hate her, the kids and I. Not - not hate her but we thought, oh, boring old thing. But - she always
 came for Christmas - on Christmas Day for the day. And there were always at least one if not two or three people like that, lonely people, to share Christmas.
