ven. As a present - prize, he was so thrilled with me, because he didn't know I was being put in for that exam. No, and neither did I. None of us knew that - anything about it. And Miss Slack who was the headmistress of this little church school in Sneint
on Dale put me in for it off her own pat, so that I can't remember anything about the exam because I didn't know it was an exam. I didn't know anything about it.
