 a crack runner in my - year at Mandella. We played games at school of course, hockey and - all those sort of things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
When you were still at school did you ever go to the theatre or just the pantomimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Went to the pantomime every year from being tiny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Other theatres?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
We wouldn't - I remember my mother taking me to my first opera when I was in my teens, II Travatoire. Oh I've never forgotten the wonder of that evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Other concerts did you go to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Only school things I should imagine. School plays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 And this one music hall your father took you to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 That was well in my teens then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 You didn't go to any others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 How old were you when you went to the opera?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 I should be in my teens.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Did you keep this up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Well, yes, I think we more or less started - going to Gilbert and Sullivan. We went to all those every night in the week. I think we went in the - we started in a decent seat and finished up in the gods as our money fizzled out. And - v
arious things like that, but we wouldn't - we wouldn't have gone to any - modern as they call it plays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Did you go to the cinema ever when you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Yes, I used to take Harry to the - matinee every Saturday. The Perils of Pauline or something. He was thrilled with it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Did your parents give you any pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Yes, we had - we started off when we were very tiny with a ha'penny. Then it went to a penny. And it gradually increased as we got older.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 What would it have been when you were at Mandella?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
I can't really remember, but - whatever I - I wouldn't be extravagant and whatever they thought I wanted they would see I had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 What sort of things did you spend your money on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Books I should think. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Can you remember anything else special?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Well of course we were all the time saving up to buy each other birthday presents and Christmas boxes and - bunches of flowers for mother on her birthday and goodness knows what and - Mother's Day and so on. But we didn't go short of anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 You were observing Mother's Day then were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
I don't know, but there was some - I know that there was some occasion when we used to give mother a bunch of flowers each, though I can't remember what it was. Something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Can you ever remember the most pocket money you got when you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
No, I can't remember. Particularly a frightful paper called the Police News, in which of course my people didn't take, but - various children we knew wo
uld get hold of one, it was pink. And - we'd try and read it, and that of course was full of all the things that are now in the ordinary daily papers. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Were you censored very much about your reading, could you tell me about the book that was hidden?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Require Invisible, yes. Yes. Oh I don't know who it was by or - or what it was about but all I know is - for some reason I wasn't allowed to read it. And I did read it in the end and I've no idea what it was about. But we - a - a paper we had by 
- edited by I think Arthur Mee, the childrens newspaper wasn't it. Something. Yes, we had that. Yes. And very good it was. Yes, it was very good. And I do remember - going into a house one day - where the children were - where the people were having a mea
l
, I believe the - I'd gone with a message for the wife and mother, and the children were all standing round the table eating which astonished me very much. And - I - I was astonished to discover that they did that. They stood, I don't know why. It says so
mething here about them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 There were enough seats were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Well I - I can't clearly remember that, but they were definitely standing.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Do you remember what sort of people they were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Well they were - they - it was a very poor home. I t
hink - I'd gone with a message for the wife to come and do some job or other at home. But I was absolutely astounded to see these people - children standing up to eat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 You don't know about this when you're little do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 No. You don't understand
 why. And of course I was much too - shy or something to say why are they standing. Some children might have done but I didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 You were probably tactful?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Yes. And of course we would - never have been allowed to got a funeral or anything like that. In fact, the idea of death altogether was really kept from us. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Do you remember anyone dying when you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Well, yes, both my grandmother's died when I was very small. But - it - as far as I was concerned it was hushed up. My - mo
ther's mother died, I was only about two and a half, and I happened to be staying there. And she - she just went to sleep during the night. And - I was very quickly sort of - shooed away and I don't know what. That was in Yorkshire. And - you know, it was
 all hushed up, I couldn't find out what was happening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 I thought that death was talked about much more in the past?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Well it wasn't - it wasn't with us, no, it wasn't with us. And it wasn't; no explanations as to why - grandma had gone or where s
he'd gone or anything. For quite a time and then they just - just - my aunt would just say, oh she's gone to heaven or something like that you know. And then - I don't - there no - I certainly had nothing to do with the funeral, and never saw anything to 
do with it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Could you tell us anything about what people wore for mourning or anything?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Oh well they'd all wear deep black of course. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 But they didn't talk about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 No, didn't talk about it. And even I should have black ribbon
s, black hair ribbons. And things like that. But it was just because grandma had gone to heaven. But it wasn't made - gloomy. It was - I can't remember the atmosphere of gloom or anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Did boys go to funerals and not girls, or didn't any children go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
No, none of - none of the children went. Oh no, we were - ever so old before we went to a funeral, and even to this day - there - their natural instinct is to stop me going. Yes. And when mother died here - I was really quite upset but I didn't s
ay anything to them because they were terribly upset. Where - mother had a stroke, and - we were - I'd just come home from the Army and the - the - Noel and Harry were still there. And when we knew she'd had a stroke we - phoned the Army and they got the 
two boys home. Very good they were. Noel was in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Norway{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
, and they got him home. And - she only - she was in a come for seven days and then she died, and we knew of course that she was skinking and - they were all sort of about and I'd gone to - they'd eviden
tly sent me to have a rest because I was pretty well chewed up, and she died while I was resting and they didn't fetch me for the end. Father and the boys - were there of course, all four of them. But not me. And - that really was their natural instinct, 
n
ot to have - any womenfolk - be too upsetting - actually I - in a way was - wasn't likely to be as much upset as they were. But I realized that - what it was, and why they'd done it so I didn't say anything But I was really rather upset. Yes. Not that it 
would have made any difference because she was unconscious all week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Can we go back to when you were three now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 I believe you said you went to school when you were three?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Yes. I went - I was three in January and I went to school a
t the Easter, I don't know why.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 I wondered why you went so early as you were the oldest sister.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Yes. As a - I should think really I should want to go. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 What sort of school did you go to first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 That little tiny - I saw it the oth
er day, a little tiny church school. On Windmill Lane in Sneinton. It was called then. The wind - the old windmill I believes still there. Oh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 They're trying to preserve it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Oh good. I'm glad. And - and although I loved school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 At three?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Yes. There was a lovely big roaring fire in the grate. And a big black bear, the rocking bear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Like a rocking horse?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Yes, but a bear, a black bear. And - and when I sat on the front - well I can remember it as clearly as anything. And we had - copy writing books.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 At three?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Well - I can't clearly remember whether I had that at three or - or whether I was older, but I can remember - it - it's all bundled together in my mind. We had - this is a thing I most clearly remember was how mu
ch I loved - copying that copperplate writing. And when we'd filled the book we were allowed to take them home. And my father used to be thrilled with - this - the way I'd copied the writing. And - very quickly I could read. Ever so quickly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Do you remember being taught to read?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
I don't really remember being taught, but I know that I could read quite quickly. I know I was taught. And - but I can't sort of remember how or what the lessons were. But at - except that we had little - books. And - we 
sort of read words. We didn't - I don't think we bothered with letters or anything. We read words straight away I think, learnt words. And I was there 'til I was seven. And then the same thing happened again, I was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Could you tell me about the girl who took you to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Well I don't - I remember she did take me backwards and forwards, she was also going you see but was very much older.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Did it take long to go to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 How long? About - about ten minutes walk I should think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 How did you feel about the teachers at your first school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Oh we loved the teachers, at least I did. And of course nobody was - naughty in those days. Every - all I remember about the classes was everybody being quiet and listening. And we learnt - a -
 we did a terrific lot of learning things off. Tables and - nursery rhymes. We learnt everything off, I know because I - when I got home I used to repeat them, tell mother them - not father so much because he was busy, but mother what I'd learnt. And I ca
n
 very well remember learning twinkle twinkle little star, because when I got home - my mother - taught me a new version of it, and I'd very much like to get to the bottom of that. Would you like me to repeat it? As much as I can remember. Scintillate, sci
ntillate globule specific, feign would I fathon thine oceans pacific, loftily poised in ether capacious, strongly resembling a gem carvenaceous.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 I know that too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Well where does it come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 I've no idea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Well I remember mother teaching me that when I was very tiny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 I thought that was a modern version.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Oh no, she taught me that when I was very tiny indeed. I wish - I wish I could find out where it comes from. - Yes. Yes. Oh and I learnt that when I was - oh, I should think five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 I thought it was very modern?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 So I got it second time around.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Yes. Yes. And she also taught us - mother had gone to a convent school when she was a girl and she taught us a lot of - little Latin - prayers and things. But I've forgotten those.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
You say you were good at your first school, what would happen if you hadn't been good?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Oh we should have - yes, if anybody was naughty they were sent to the - headmistreess whose name was Miss Slack I remember. And - what -
 I don't know what - of course she did or - gave them a good smack I should think because they - if anybody was slightly naughty the teacher would give them a slap.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 On the hand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Yes, I can't remember, no. And I - I think there was a cane on the
 desk but I don't ever remember it being used. You know, she'd sometimes tap on the - desk if - people were talking a bit, but there was - on the whole I'm sure the children were good, they were probably more awed than - anything, because the teachers in 
those days were very authoritative. They - the minute they came in they had authority and everybody was quite immediately.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
At your first school did the other children come from similar sorts of homes to your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 I think so because - Sneinton Val
e in those days was - was really a little village. With fields and - trees all round. Very pretty it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Do you know anything about school fees at that first school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
School fees? No there were no fees. No, it was a church school, and there was - I don't think there was anything to pay.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Did the teachers single out some children for different treatment to the other children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Oh I think they did. I think they - bothered with those who were - who they thought were - going to be good or el
se - how could they have - got me through a - a scholarship. They must have bothered with me, I don't remember them doing so but they must have bothered with me a bit. Mustn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Were you the first girl to get a scholarship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Oh I don't know. 
All I know is that I got a scholarship. I didn't know I was going in for a scholarship. And neither did my parents. But - one day Miss Slack - came to me and - and said - she - I'm going to your home, you come with me now and she took me down home, and sh
e said to father, she's won a scholarship for Mandella. I've come to see if you agree to her going. And I remember that ever so well and I - I can almost remember pricking my ears up when I heard this word - news.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 So it was a surprise?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Yes. It wa
s. And I can remember father's delight and pleasure. And he said, oh yes, certainly she can go. And - he bought me a piano as a present, 'cos I'd passed. Because - the scholarship included music. We had - a lot of singing and; piano playing at school. And
 sing - a lot of singing and - learning things and - I seem - to remember quite a bit about music. I don't quite know what it was, singing and that sort of thing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 When you went to Mandella how long did it take you to get there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Oh about twenty minutes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Did you come home for the middle of the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Mostly we - stayed at school. It was I think fivepence for lunch. Or - or you could take your own sandwiches. Sometimes I did one and sometimes the other, I don't know why. But by then we'd moved to Bridgford and I was going from Bridgford to Mandella.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 So part of the time you would have done one and part the other would you?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Was Mandella a mixed school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Yes. A very good school. Excellent education. Yes, both boys and 
girls. Very small classes, none of the classes had more than about - the class I was in I think had twenty-four. I don't think any of them had more than thirty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 When you were at Bridgford and went to Mandella how did you get there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Walk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Just the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 How long did it take then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Oh only about quarter of an hour, twenty minutes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 It didn't make much difference then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 What were the school hours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Nine to twelve and two to - half past four I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 What did you think of that school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Oh - wonderful. All the staff were - all degree people of course in those days. And real degrees not these tuppenny ha'penny things they have - go in for today. And they were all enthusiasts on their particular 
subject. Each - each one taught a particular subject, although you were in a form - the form I was in - the - form master specialized in maths, at which I was very bad. And then all the others had their own particular subjects and would go round. And they
 were all enthusiasts, so that every subject - was interesting. The - I can always remember the geography }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15033757\charrsid11885113 mistress}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 , she was a wizard, Miss Lawrence. She made geography really thrilling, I mean a subject like that Not like history with - but geography she co
uld make thrilling. Oh it was a very good school. In fact I met somebody in Cambridge the other - last - one day last year, I was down there for - staying with a friend for a weekend - and they said that the - the education that was given at Mandella in t
hose days, there was no finer in this country. Yes. And of course the honours board were - the hall - hall was full of honours boards. No end of them got in it every year.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Apart from the actual teaching of subjects, did the teachers emphasise certain things as important in life? Things like manners, tidiness, punctuality?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Oh yes, even walking. Even walking, if any - nobody was allowed to slouch in school. And - we had - if anybody was inclined to slouch you had to walk round the hall on tip-toes.
 So that - and they - during the - some sort of - department or something like that and - you had to walk - and keep perfectly upright. Oh yes, and they all -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Books on heads?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Yes, sometimes books on heads, yes. And - manners of course was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 What would happen if you were late at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Well you - you'd be ticked off but not very severely. Occasionally I was late, and you were ticked off but not really severely. Never were much late.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 What would happen there if you did something the teachers disapproved of?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Well I don't know, see, for one thing - all the pupils there were keen on work. If - if they found somebody who wasn't keen on work they asked the parents to take them away. That happened to my - one of my brothers. Yes. He 
- yes, Frank. He was - he'd won a scholarship and gone to Mandella, and after he'd been there a year - they sent for pop, and they said - your boy is not the academic type. He's not interested in - he's terribly interested in sports and games, and all tha
t side, he's not interested in the other side. And this school concentrates on the other, so do you mind moving him. And - pop moved - took him away and sent him to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 So they punished you by the threat of removal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Yes, but they didn't - it didn't
 sound like a punishment, it just sounded like a -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 What was more suitable.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Yes, what was more suitable.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Can you tell me anything about punishments at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Well we had an awful lot of impositions. You know, they thought nothing of - g
iving you - a hundred or even five hundred lines of Shakespeare to write out or something like that. And I remember one day when - for some reason, I don't know why, the staff had been called suddenly to a meeting, and - the form we happened to be in at t
h
e time, there were - about ten boys and about ten girls, and some of them after a little while started playing up and suddenly the form master put his head round the door and he said, all the boys five hundred lines of Shakespeare, and went out again. So 
they all got their -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Just the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Boys. They all got their jotters out, and each girl went and sat by a boy and was reading the Shakespeare like mad and they were scribbling it down. And he came in, put his head round the door again and he said
, if the girls are on your side I'll let you off. But the - the - the - the staff and the - children were - the students were friendly, there was a friendly atmosphere. I remember this same form master discovered that I was mad on reading, and liked to re
a
d more or less anything, and - he - unobtrusively arranged for me to have a key to the library. So I could go and help myself. And - yes, and - oh there was lots of - sort of similar instants - incidents with various members of the staff and the pupils. A
 very good -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Can you remember any physical punishment ever?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 No. I shouldn't think there'd be any.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 So boys and girls were treated alike there were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
More or less, yes. Yes, more or less. I don't know of course what happened to the b
oys if they were called in to the head. But they were - a - another thing - show you the spirit of the school, during the lunch hour - there were two - boys, both of whom were killed in the first world war, who were brilliant musicians. And during the lun
ch hour they were allowed to go and play - on the piano if they wanted to. And quite often - a little - groups of us would go and sit round in the hall, and listen to them playing during the lunch hour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Were your parents interested in your school work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Oh very. Yes, very. We had an awful lot of homework of course. Oh a terrific lot. Every night. At least I had - I - it took me every night because probably I wasn't as quick as some of my - girlfriends who were really - from a school point of view a
t any rate, were more brainy.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 In those days did parents visit the school ever?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Well we had a - we had a - a day - one day a year when we all went and did goodness knows what at the Mechanics - Institute on the stage.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 A sort of speech day was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Yes, and all that sort of thing, and prizes. Prize day it was really. Of course there were a lot of prizes, and - in all sorts of subjects - and - a dancing display and a drill display, and all that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Did your parents ever go to the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
I can't really remember them going to the - I don't think any parents ever came to school. No. I can't remember them ever going to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Did your parents ever meet the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Well they must have - met them - sometime b
ecause - I can remember odd things they said about them, but I can't remember them meeting them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
At that school did the other children there come from similar types of home to your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Oh yes, all very similar. There were a few - very poor - bu
t very clever children who were there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 How did they fit in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Oh they fitted in very well. Fitted in perfectly well but - I can remember I used to feel a bit sorry for them because they were a bit shabby and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Did you have school uniform?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Yes, we had a school uniform. They had that of course. But you know they probably wouldn't have it renewed as often as we would and such like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Did the teachers there single out some children for different treatment compared with the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Not particularly, I don't think.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Were there any gangs in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Were there any children who were left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Well I can't remember ever - any that were particularly. See the classes weren't very
 big, and you were all friendly. And - with - in - with your - in your own year you all sort of were friendly with each other and knew each other, there weren't very many of you
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 How long did you stay there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 I stayed there 'til I was seventeen I 
think. Of course by then the war had broken out. And that upset everything. Oh what a shocking war that was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 So what happened to you when you were seventeen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Well, I - all - I left - I left school and I went to - for a - well, as long as the war was on I did a sort of secretarial job with a friend of my father's.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Had you had any training for this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
No. But - I - it wasn't so difficult. Of course the - typing and that sort of thing was only just coming in, in fact I can remember that the
 head of this firm flatly refused to have a typewriter. He'd never had had one and he wasn't going to have one. And he still used his own letterpress.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 So you got this very first job through your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Can you tell me what exactly you did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Yes, I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15033757\charrsid11885113 don\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
 know how - I did it really. It was - to do with cotton. With a cotton mill. And - I was - spent most of my time working out most complicated wages.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 And you said you were bad at maths?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Yes. But - most complicated wage
s, you know - a thousand - something or others, for instance - at - a penny farthing for twenty-five or - forty-two - it was - the most terribly complicated. And I and a - a young - chap of about - eighteen or so, we worked them all out, and then they wer
e
 - so many of them were roughly checked with - by the head clerk of the office. It was very complicated, oh and another thing I did was - on - you see I'd learnt French at Mandella - or - not much but I'd learnt French, and - I answered the French, they h
ad a French connection, I answered the French letters. Must have been awful French but anyhow I did it. Any rate - they evidently carried on.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 What hours did you work in this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Oh I don't know, nine 'til one I should think and - probably two t
o - half past five. The mill hours of course would be slightly different from that, they'd start at six or something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 You'd do office hours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 We weren't allowed to go into the mill Christmas week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Because they - were all celebrati
ng. Yes, I wasn't allowed to go in the mill at all. The whole of Christmas week they were - they were all - more or less tight I should think, they had port - and something else. Bottles of port they all used to drink all week, and quite a - they were qui
te merry and bright. Anyhow it was strictly forbidden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Because you were a young girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Because I was a young girl and not allowed into the mill. The whole of the week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 I've met people that were working in the mill but they haven't told me thi
s bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
No. Oh yes, they were the - the - 'course the - the - not the head of the firm but the manager was a great friend of father's, lifelong friend of pop's, and of course he was very anxious that nothing - should happen to me or that I shouldn't s
ee anything that I shouldn't see etcetera.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Did you work Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Saturday morning at the office, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 I don't suppose you had holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Can you remember what you were paid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Twelve and six I think.
 Seven and six the first week I went and then very quickly - after a week or two I got twelve and six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Did you feel at the time that that was a fair wage?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Oh I think so, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Did you give any of the money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 I can't reme
mber. I probably did because the war was on, and - you see, pop would have lost his business and had to go to the - war. Be called up. It was the end of the war. He'd been called up and we were really practically ruined because - his - the whole of his li
ving went you see. So any - and I was the only one that was - that had left school, so I should imagine that we all - that I forked out what I earnt to help things along.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 How did you get along with the other people you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Oh all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 From what you said your employer treated you very well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Oh yes, because - he -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 How did you feel about him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Oh he was a very - nice man, very -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 How did you feel about the work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Oh I quite enjoyed it. It was hard work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 You didn't have any job before you left school did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 How long did you stay in this one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Well, 'til the war was over. Be about eighteen months I should think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 And then what happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 And then I went to - Poly High for teach
ing. They started a - started a scheme for all those people who'd wanted to be teachers and had been stopped because of the war, and - I heard about it and joined it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Where was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 It was mostly at - a technical college of something at Hucknall
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 It was a local one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Yes, it's a {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}county{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}coun{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 - it was a County Council arrangement. And we - we did - what they used to call then pupil teaching, two days a week, and studying the other three. And Saturday morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Was it a long course?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
It was a two year course but it had been running six months when I - got in it. And then the - we were examined at the end and - took our certificates at the end. Most of us got through.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 So you only did eighteen months?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Yes, because they we
re short of teachers you see. So I must think they pushed a lot of us through. Although one of - one of my friends didn't get through, that was going - that went with me every day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Had you taken any special exams when you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 O
nly the ordinary - school certificate and that sort of thing, I forget what they called it then. Metric exemption didn't they? Yes, metric exemption I think. Yes. Really forgotten. The war - over - awed everything. Your mind was filled with the war to the
 
exclusion - because of the horrors of it. Those awful newspapers every day with - filled with - lists of dead. I can - now I can see people standing in the streets and looking through the lists to see if their - menfolk were there. And suddenly hearing a 
w
oman scream when she saw - husband or somebody killed and - one - one woman who - we were just - I was just crossing Trent Bridge, and she suddenly gave a frightful scream and went to throw herself over the - bridge but - the people of course stopped her.
 Her husband was killed, she lived near us and - and I knew her and her two boys. I often wonder what's become of them. Oh yes, it was too horrifying was the war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Can you tell me about what you did after your teaching training? Did you go straight into teaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Yes, I went straight into teaching. Where did I teach first? Oh I went to the church school at Hucknall. My first - two - you had to teach - after you'd taken this you had to teach for two years under the County, because it was the County 
scheme, and I went to Hucknall church school for two years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Can you remember what you were paid there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Oh I - I can't really remember, something like seven pounds a month. Six pounds a month or something like that, can't remember really. And - m
y word we did have to work I had - I started - I was a raw teacher, and I had - forty-five children to begin with and by the end of the - year, there were - nearly eighty babies - four or five - four and five year olds in that class because - as they reac
hed an age they were allowed to come to school.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 And you had the intake?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
I was in charge of them. And I can't - I can't - I've no recollection of it being - of it overwhelming me or anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 You don't?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 No. I - I have no recollection w
hatever of it - of - finding it more than I could cope with. I know that I always used to be terribly exhausted when I got home. I used to get home and flop into a - chair and mother would quickly provide me with a cup of tea or - I didn't move for quite 
a
 while, I was done up, yes. And - we - as well as having that, I also had to stay when my - of course the babies class went home - four, at four o'clock. Then I had to get - stay for an extra half an hour and play the piano for some other classes - teache
r
 taking something, dancing or singing or music or some sort of thing. I used to be - furious at that because it meant I missed a - the train that I could have caught and had to wait three quarters of an hour for the next. So I didn't get home until about 
h
alf past six. You see it was all expected, the headmistress there was no good. No, she was hopeless, she never did a stroke of work, she was altogether hopeless. But the - first assistant they called them in those days, she was - very much all there, and 
s
he ran the school. But the headmistress had gone - as a girl, when it had been a little country church school with about twenty-five pupils. She'd remained there although she'd grown and grown - grown with the collierygrowth. But she - she hadn't grown wi
th it, she was - really just a simple country girl.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 How did you get on with your colleagues?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 With who?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 The other teachers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Oh, very friendly with them all. I remember them well. I was very friendly with them all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 How long were you there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
I was - I was in - I did my two years there, you have to do two years. It was compulsory in your first school. And then I applied to come to Nottingham, to a {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Nottingham{\*\xmlclose}
 school and I came. And I think I went to Leeside. That was an interesting
 school, and the headmistress was marvelous. And the staff. They were. Of course all slum children from 'the Market and all round there. But the headmistress had them all disciplined. Very good school indeed man we all had to stay every lunchtime to serve
 
them with meals because they were all poor children. And nobody objected that I ever heard of. We took it in turns, I think alternate days, staying to - serve their meals. I always remember when - famous day when a little boy was crying. And I said to him
, what are you crying for? He'd come in late, I said, where have you been, what are you crying for? He said -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Can you tell me how you were taught to teach more at your second school than during your training?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Well - say for instance you would - 
say she was going to give a history lesson, she'd get perhaps - a - a big - a lot of illustrations of the period of history she was going to - and she would - not just stand in front of the class and tell them a piece of history, you connect every item, e
v
ery sentence with something they could see as well. Remember these were all slum children. And - and she would - make them perhaps find something on this, she'd say something and make them find something on this which - that - illustrated it. And she kept
 them all sort of on their toes all the time. And - all that sort of thing, and whatever she did she did something practical as well as talking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 So you think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Yes. Yes. Then she would - and she wouldn't bother any - with you anymore that day but 
then another - later on, perhaps days later or a week or two later - she'd come back and hear you give a similar lesson. And then - she'd - criticize it but in a very nice way. Oh yes, she was - splendid, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 So how long were you there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 I can't remember. About two years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 And then where? Were you going up in salary during this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Yes, I think we had an increase every year didn't we. I think so, I'm not certain.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Where did you go next?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 I think I went to - I think they moved
 me then, I don't think they ever kept anybody very long at this place - school. I think they moved me to - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Dale Gibson Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} or Lenton somewhere.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Another similar school or was it posher?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Yes. Well not such a strain, not such a big - difficult ch
ildren in class, because the children were of course difficult. Because they were - so bewildered }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15033757\charrsid11885113 with}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113  life and circumstances, living such awful conditions. We were - they were all supplied with boots or shoes. Yes. If they hadn't any boots or shoes they w
ere supplied with them. And they were supplied with all their meals at lunchtime.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 This was all through the headmistress?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 All through the - the - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}County
{\*\xmlclose} Council.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 But who would decide they needed boots or shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Oh I should think she would, I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 I wondered if they had a special kind of office to deal with this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
No, I don't - I - I wouldn't know, all I know is that you know - they really, I think if we - if they had a child come to school in our class - we would repor
t their - to the headmistress, haven't got any shoes. Quite often they'd come without any shoes or stockings. And - then they would be supplied with them, that's all I know. Well then in - in the meantime I'd - broken off my engagement so I went to Spurn 
Point, to get - away from everybody and everything because of this awful - break up, and I - I happened to hear - my uncle in the Army had got some connection with - the military unit at - \{BLANK\}
 - and my aunt wrote one day and said, that - they want a - t
eacher for the school, the present one's gone out of her mind or something. And - although she hadn't thought of - she was only telling mother this as a point of interest - I said, oh I'm going to apply for it and I'm going. And I - and I went. Yes, Spurn
 Point in Yorkshire. And I stayed there, I - I really went for six months while they got a new teacher but I stayed eighteen months, I loved it. And I had the little school with about - twelve pupils.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 And you were the boss?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Yes, I was the only on
e. And they were all ages from - four to fourteen. And oh I had a lovely time. They begged me to stay. I really thoroughly enjoyed organising it and - and running it. Of course like all isolated places you meet a lot of interesting people. More of that - 
I've proved that several times. The more isolated the place the more interesting people you meet. All sorts of odd people coming and going. And - I stayed there - for eighteen months or nearly two years I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 What stage had you got to roughly now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Big strike. 1926. It was while I was there the big strike was on. And - in the meantime my uncle - had become - Army uncle had become paralysed. Through some war injury or other - or other and - he built a bungalow, he had - had a bungalow built At Sp
urn. He came there because he was very sensitive about being paralysed. And he came there and - of course all - our two families, mother was his sister, had always spent a lot of time together, there - we all spent all our holidays there every year. Very 
nice it was too. Well then I came back to Nottingham and - decided I was fed up with this - ordinary teaching, I wanted to see more of the world And I went to South Africa.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 That's about 1927 is it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 It was - must have been a bit later than that, 
perhaps about 1930, can't remember now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Would you have a gap doing nothing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 No, I stayed - I - I taught, I can't remember - where I went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 In Nottingham?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
It's - in Nottingham anyway. Oh I - I'm not sure I wasn't at I think I went to South Africa from a school at
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 What were you doing in South Africa?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Did you have any cause to go there rather than anywhere else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
No, the thing was I went to - somewhere, would it be the overseas - something to do with the overseas people or there or - I think I went up to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 and saw the Overseas Club people. And I said to them - I wanted to go abroad for a few years, I didn't really mind where I went. And - talked about various places, in the end they said, are you willing to 
do any jobs? As much - you see, I said, no, I - I'm willing to do anything. I don't mind what I do as long as I can work my way about. So they said, well if you like to go to Capetown we can fix you up with - a - all sorts of odd jobs there. And - so I sa
i
d, right, I'll go, and I went. And I went to Capetown and the - Secretary of the Overseas Club came on the boat to meet me which I thought was very nice. And I went to the club and - the first job I had there was - coaching a boy for school. Very interest
i
ng family. He was a - he was old enough - he had all sorts of odd people, they were quite mad the Maltino's, all of them. The - the grand - father, would be the great-grandfather - was the first Prime Minister of South Africa. Yes. And - he'd gone out wit
h the boy - and started a little wine business and of course the - at a very early date in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}South Africa{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 - brought up various farms lands and all sorts of things like that. And then they started making the railway, of course he made a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15033757\charrsid11885113 fortune}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 . And - this was
 his - don't know whether it was granddaughter now or great-granddaughter. I met her at the club and she asked me if I'd go and coach - her son, because he ought to go to school and he wasn't ready. And I went and stayed with them for six months, coaching
. He - he went to the - what was called the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Boys{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}High School{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 in Capetown. He got into - into the school. Well then I - there was also a {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Girls{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}High School{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose}. St Ciprians it was called in the days when all the - wealthy people sent their girls, and - I got a - 
a - I got a temporary job on the staff there. That was interesting, but the headmistress was a shocker. Oh. A snob, a most terrible snob. And of course I - was nauseated with that. So much so that one member of the staff who was - hard up and - you know, 
p
oor sort of way, parents had both died, she treated her shockingly, purely because she was poor, and hard up. She was a good teacher - and I - I never left this girl alone, I said, you - you - you're to leave this school even - even - even if it means red
u
ced salary. You're to leave this school and go somewhere else because your life's hell here. It was quite definitely hell. And not while I was there but after I'd - gone, she wrote and told me she'd got away. And she said, it's entirely due to your pushin
g that I made the effort. She was cowered with this awful woman. Connected with all the - ecclesiastical higheads in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}England{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
. And not - a cruel knock. Horrible.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 How long did you stay there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Oh I was only there about six months, I had a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15033757\charrsid11885113 temporary}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
 job. Well then - the - the Chairwoman of the - Overseas Club - came to me one day and said - that - the Gov - the old Government House - was being used as a - what you call it, I don't know - what you call it, a home for abandoned children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Orphanage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
In a way, yes. And - the - woman who'd been running it - was absolutely at the end of her tether, she was a mad Irish woman. And - would I - she said, it's a terrible job, I warn you, it'll be an awful job, but will you go - for at any rate six mon
ths and give her a hand? So I said, all right, I will. Well - I could write six books about that place. I've never come across anything like it, it was a disgrace to \{BLANK\}
 It was a huge - building with massive grounds, hundreds of acres, and no - fence o
r anything, what there had been originally was broken down, a neglected shabby place, practically empty of furniture. I don't think we ever went to bed for more than two or three hours. Every single night without exception the police brought in - newborn 
babies, born on {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Table{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Mountain{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
. Every night. And there was a - a big room at the end with a lot of beds, and all these new babies were put in, there was a black woman and two black }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15033757\charrsid11885113 girls}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113  who were in charge, whether they knew anything about babies nobody kno
ws. They hadn't time to bother. You just took the baby along and it was - full of children, and there were people, boys and girls of all ages from new born babies - to twenty years old, in that one place, nobody did - to do anything for them but we two. T
here were a few - there were two or three - native - women.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 How many children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Oh there must have been - anything - it varied terrifically, I'll explain why in a minute. Fifty - perhaps - even perhaps average about fifty, but sometimes you'd have
 another twenty more. Because - when they - got into their ear - very early teens - the Capetown authorities found jobs for them, they never bothered whether the jobs were suitable, or where they were, and they - they - every day so many would go to these
 
jobs and - every day so many came back. Run away. And every night - so many children ran away, and everyday the police came and - collected - brought some back and the others went. It was hell. And - there were two English women who were supposed to come 
every day, and teach, mind you there were - I - I agree they were practically }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15033757\charrsid11885113 untouchable}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 , anyway they could have - done something with them but they did damn all those two women. And they were paid to teach by the Capetown authority. And they were - they w
ere both I think in their fifties. And oh I was furious with them. They never did anything, they just let them - run riot. And they didn't arrange anything or do anything, just paint until it was time to go and went, always hours er - before they should h
a
ve done. They were hopeless, but I suppose their hearts had been broken probably, because it was terrible. We never sat down to a meal, we just snatched anything to eat we could. I lost I think two stone in the six months I was there - at least. I was thi
n
 as a rail when I left. Well - I got the - several of the staff at St Ciprians school - to come and - in their spare time, and they came - to redecorate a couple of rooms. And this particular teacher who had been so badly treated by the head, she was - qu
i
te a good artist, and she painted the - she painted the whole of this nursery where all the babies were with nursery pictures round, and a big - another big room that was used for a dining room - she painted a mural all round that, and these - three or fo
ur of them came in their spare time until they'd - redecorated a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15033757\charrsid11885113 couple}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113  of the rooms, just roughly - what - what do you call it now. Yes. Quite. All out of their own pockets, of course, there was no funds for these things. And - there was not staff to do an
ything. They - the girls had to sort of wash their - clothes and - there was a black - woman who - somehow organised something to eat, very simple, nothing much in the way of food. The quantity was all right but it was - nothing much and we had no time to
 
- to bother with what they were having. And there were no beds, they all slept on the floor in just a blan - couple of blankets. One to sleep on the other to cover them. And outside - there was a great - sort of well, surrounded by tape, with iron railing
s
 round the top, what it had been originally I can't think. unless it had been a prison or something, but all the boys were there, sitting at these tables, most of the day were sat there doing nothing. And there was a - native - chap who was supposed to be
 in charge of them, he was a chap in his early thirties and he'd been sent they tell me because he'd been the star pupil at the mission school \{BLANK\}
 and from the first look at him I knew that that chap was no good. And he used to stand there by this raili
ng, looking down at the boys, cracking a whip. A great - a long whip with a great long stock. And so I - I just called out one day, I said, if ever I see you using that whip - you will be for it. I shall get rid of you. No matter what it costs. But anyhow
,
 I said, what are these boys doing, why can't you arrange to do something with them? In the grounds or something like that. It doesn't matter whether it matters or not, just do something. Oh, it's because they can't do anything, he said. No - I got - a - 
I
 got a - from somewhere, I don't know where - a lot of - spades and - shovels and things like that, and I said to the boys, come on, you can all help make a start. Well there was about a hundred acres of ground, and it was all wild. Overgrown and shocking
.
 But - just to keep them occupied, I told them they'd got to dig up all this - all - a great big square ground which I marked off, you know, to give them a goal, an object. And they really enjoyed doing it. And day after day these poor things - were diggi
ng all this stuff and ground up. What it looked like when they'd finished I don't know. But - very quickly we found that - the chap was - not only seducing all the girls but the boys as well. I knew he was no good the minute I looked at him.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 You could tell?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Yes. So of course he was - oh they were horrified, he's our star pupil. He was a star pupil at there. But you - you see the - he'd just been given too much power too quickly. And he - it just sort of undermined him. He'd been - he'd been doing
 as he liked. And - nobody - there was nobody to - no supper - form of superintendant at all. We co - first thing every morning we collected them all together - in the - in a sort of hall - entrance, and - they all sang a hymn and we had a prayer, quite m
eaningless of course. And - I - through these people I'd got to know at the Overseas Club and St Ciprians school I collected an enormous number of - childrens - books, small childrens books, all pictures, and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15033757\charrsid11885113 jigsaws}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 , simple jigsaw puzzles, and \{BLANK\} and 
they - they liked that but they didn't want to do anything for more than a very short time. And they - they were all unhappy. An awful feeling of - frustration, of misery in the whole place. And - no end of times I would try - to persuade a girl to go and
 take a job which I could easily have got for her - as a - a maid in a nice home, and the poor things, all they could say was, oh no, get married. Mm. That's all they could - all they could think of was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 How long did you stick here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Oh dear. The
 first morning that I woke up, I was covered from head to foot in flea bites. Millions of flea bites from head to foot. It even - although I was - by now pretty tough it - it even made the tears come to my eyes to think - covered. But of course after a ti
me they stopped biting. I gave it up in despair I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 So what did you do next?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Well - after I'd been there - six or eight months and of course - lots of things that I'd done and said had begun to seep through - to the authorities, and a commit
tee was called, and they got two poor muts from England, a young curate and his wife - to say they'd go out and help to run the place. I often wonder how soon their hearts were broken. And then the - Capetown women, who - who really \{BLANK\}
 formed a commit
tee. And I couldn't help but laugh, they came - the first time they came they brought a lot of - very pretty little baby - clothes and things. You know, their - their attitude was - wrong for what it was. It wanted something much more robust and much more
 
down to earth. But they probably thought that out eventually. But at any rate they had a committee formed and they got these two - extra people from England, and - I think they must have - started - trying to do something - properly, but oh dear, the shoc
k
ing problems there. Really shocking. We just used to - snatch something to eat or - or go - and have a couple of hours on the bed, and we could - alternately, I remember one day - one - early one morning about three in the morning, the police - brought in
 
a little thing they'd found in a cave. And it was thick with black - they'd found it in a cave with a native girl, she was dead, been dead several days before they found her. And they brought this little thing in, it was covered with bites and covered wit
h
 dirt. It really gave you the horrors to see it. Well, of course - we set to and - after about a week - got it clean and it was a white - white child. A white child, very pretty too. Before I came away it really looked a little - dream. But that was the s
ort of thing that was happening every week, every few days. But every night - at least one baby came every night, without - fail.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Where had they been found?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
On Table Mountain most of them. Yes, yes, because Government House is at the foot of {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Table{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Mountain{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose}. And the police brought them of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 So what did you do next?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
I - I left there and I went to Johannesburg, I - also the - through the Overseas Club again - asked me if I'd - like to take a - soft job - this job there. I said, yes,
 I would. Well she said - one of the Johannesburg millionaires, he wants his son to go to Rugby, and he will - he wants some - English woman, English girl to go and - get him used to English ways really is what it amounted to. Would you like to go? So I s
aid, yes, I'll go. I went, of course I had a marvellous time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 What did you have to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
I went - I didn't do anything. When I come to think - you know, yes, I put on three stone while I was there. Because when I'd - been there a little while I wen
t - I was supposed to go for three months but I stayed eighteen, and - after I'd - seen about where Clive had got to mentally and all the rest of it - his father said, do you think it'd be a good idea if I - if I sent him to the Johannesburg high - Boys H
igh School? And I said, yes, I think it would. To get him used to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 How old was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
He was - eleven. And so he went. And of course I said - I'll pack up now then, so he said, oh no, don't go yet because, this that and the other. Everytime I
 wanted to go there was some reason why I must stay a bit longer. In the end I was there eighteen months. It was very interesting. Wherever they went I went. We went to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Durban
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} for a month. Went to Capetown for a couple of months. In - Capetown we went to - can't think of the - name of the bay. There's a big hotel and - they'd booked the whole of the ground floor of the hotel. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 What did you do next?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 And they had a - came home. War broke - Mr Vennel had a phone call to 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} every evening at eight o'clock, from Jo'burg, for the latest news. And - he - he used to say, come and - sit in and hear the latest news from 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}England{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. And one night he turned to me and said, in a month or two war will be declared. And when the phone call was over he said, 
now, he said - said, there's }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15033757\charrsid11885113 definitely}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
 going to be a war. Now, he said, what do you want to do? What would you like to do, he said. Anywhere in the world you want to go I'll fix you up. Well, I said, if there's a war, I said, I've got four brothers. And i
f there's a war I want to go home. So next day he got all the tickets, and I came home. Joined the Army.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
You told me before about the parents or grandparents from Narrow Marsh, could you tell me that again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Oh that was while I was at St Ciprians
. Well the - it was parents day at St Ciprians and the - all the parents came - in - Rolls Royces and Bentlyes and Jags and goodness knows what, and suddenly I saw one of the girls, Joan something or other - crying and I said, what's the matter Joan? She 
s
aid, look, there's my grandparents in that old broken down car, and all the other girls will laugh together. And they would because it was a snobbish school. And - her parents - her grandparents got out of the war, and came up the steps to where we were t
a
lking, they said, what's Joan crying for? And suddenly her grandmother realized why she was crying, before anybody said a word. Oh, she said, oh how stupid of me. She said, why we didn't we hire a car. She said, this is our old - it does for us up - where
 we live out in the country, she said, why didn't I hire a posh car just to come here today, I never thought of it. But, she said, you know - we come a long way - for Joan to be here. And - I said, where do you come from? She said, 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Nottingham{\*\xmlclose}. I said, so do
 I. She said, you won't know where the part where I come from. I said, where is it? Narrow Marsh. I said, I do know it. Well, she said, my husband and I were born in Narrow Marsh, terrible position, and we both made up our minds - to get married and come 
o
ut to South Africa, and we were determined - that we'd have a better life for our children than ever we did when we were young, and she said, we came out and we worked hard and we've done quite reasonably well, and our children are doing very well indeed,
 
and Joan is our granddaughter, as you can see at the school. And every now and again - something like this gives the show away. She said, I wouldn't have had it happen for the world. I just didn't think quick enough. I thought that was a - a wonderful sto
ry. Yes. Yes. I can't remember their names, the girl's name was Joan, but I can't remember any other name.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 So then you went into the A.T.S. was it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 The - yes, A.T.S.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Were you there from pre-war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 No. No, war had broken out. I was at ho
me - I - after I came home - can't remember - the war broke out just after I got home I think. And - I stayed at home for a time. As a matter of fact I was having a lot of teeth out. And then I said I'm going to join up. And I really wanted to join the Na
v
y because - all our people have always been Navy people, on both mother and father's side. I suppose we've got that instinct, we all - want - if you want to do anything you want to join the Navy. But - when I went down to join the - the Navy list was clos
ed. So of course me being impatient, I couldn't wait and thought oh it's going to be years before there's a gap, actually it was only a month or two. So I went across the - to the A.T.S.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 And of course all the - they were all volunteers - at that time.
 And we were - oh we went to Saltdean, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Brighton{\*\xmlclose}
, for three weeks training. For the - the women who trained us were marvelous women. But - training was completely natural, you see we were all in civvies, and - a lot of them had got high heels and all the re
st of it, they taught us to march and to drill and do all sorts of - kind of things and taught us about gas and - lectures about this, that and the other, instructions and all the rest of it, we were measured for uniforms - and - \{BLANK\}
 But you weren't allowed out you see. And - it was three completely hectic weeks, in fact I think I - we all more or less fell in a - \{BLANK\}
 before the three weeks was up, because it was too strenuous. Definitely far too strenuous. But however, we - they were all a - a grand bunch of girls, that first lot \{BLANK\}
 And - we all more or less recovered. Well then we were all fixed up with uniforms and - a few of us were going to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}France{\*\xmlclose}, were going to be shipped over to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}
}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}France{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. And it was suddenly stopped, I can't remember why now. Held up. And then we went to - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Margate{\*\xmlclose}
, and while we were there - James Joyce said on the wireless - I heard him, we all heard him - that he was going to bomb the A.T.S., so the A.T.S. had moved to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Margate{\*\xmlclose}
 and were going to bomb them, and we were moved in the night from there to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Worthing{\*\xmlclose}
 - during the night. A long train journey with no corridor and no water and about sixteen in a carriage. It was terrible. All the girls that were in ' involved in that have never forgotten that awful journey. And we staye
d in Worthing for a few - week - and then I think I went to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Edinburgh{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} to take my commission.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 So you got your commission after how many months?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Oh I can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Quite quickly was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Perhaps - oh I don't know. Six months, I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 How long were you in the A.T.S.?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 In - I - stayed in 'til the end of the war of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Much after the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 No - only until all my girls were demobbed and then I was demobbed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 What were you by the end, something very grand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
What did they call it in those days - Senior Commander. Acting Senior Commander, that's what I was, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Did you enjoy it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Oh yes, I enjoyed it all very much. And so did most of the girls, all of them I should think, they - the thing was t
hey all had - opportunities - to express themselves that they never would have got in civilian life. Mean quite a few of my girls were - became highly qualified electricians, some of - who'd been in a hat factory in Luton or something like that before or 
g
overness or maids, and they suddenly found they'd no idea they - they could - they were capable of - what they were capable of. I remember two of my girls, the Colonel in charge of the - R.E.M.E. lot, he said they could - fix a tank up with electricity be
tter than his men. And these - yes, they'd been - next to nothing before the war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Did you do anything after you came out of the A.T.S.?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
No, because you see I'd only been home a week and mother died. So I stayed at home ever since. Oh I wouldn't h
ave left my father, he was too - he was bowled out of course, he never recovered from mother's death. We knew he wouldn't. They'd been - a devoted pair all their lives, they'd known each other since they were eighteen, he just couldn't - live without her,
 so he - he lingered for about eighteen months, two years anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
About these jobs you've done in your life, would you have preferred any other occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Well when I was at school I wanted to be a research chemist. I very much wanted to be a re
search chemist and I took - I specialized in chemistry for a couple of years. But - I had some serious trouble with my eyes. I've always said a - above the neck it's been nothing but a damn nuisance, now it's my ears, and for - eighteen months - I had to 
have my eyes - covered during artificial light. And then it - it prevented me going on with this chemical research business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 But you would like to have done that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
I'd like to have done that, yes. But - I - I've got - I've obviously got a - a restless sort of nature, I want a lot of experiences. I couldn't be - live in a rut you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Did you ever join a professional organization, a teachers union or anything?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 No, I don't think I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 In any of the jobs you did }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15033757\charrsid11885113 did}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113  you feel that th
e employers and the workers had the same interests or different? It's a bit difficult for you to answer this question isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Yes. No, I didn't - I didn't have that feeling. I thought - I - in all the jobs I've done I've very much had the feeling that there were - was quite a good connection.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 What about when you were young and working in a factory?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Well of course the factory was very separate from the staff. It was a - it was a world of its own with its own men in charge of it, all of who
m were rather frightening people from my point of view. But none of them would have said boo to me of course. Would have been out on their ears if they had, of course in those days they could give them the sack at a minute's notice. I used to like going r
ound the mill but I could only go - have - pick my time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Did you think about this sort of question when you were working there, whether there were divisions of interest among the workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Well I think - as far as that cotton mill was concerned - 
the conditions under which they worked were not very pleasant - and although I think there was a spirit of backing each other up as workers I think a lot of them fell out a lot. I think there were a lot of rows, quite serious ones.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Did you know anythi
ng about whether there was a division between the trained craftsmen and other workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
I can't really say. I do - the two Miss Russells from Wooland, I think they were both Miss Russell - the - they - were they the Middleton family or the Rupper fami
ly - some - one of those - important Woolland families, the two Miss Russells ran a - they used to come once every - every Friday, and - get a lot - talk to all the women and girls, I suppose they were trying to - do them a bit of good, and they had a tot
tering time. Very difficult time. They were - the - the - the girls and the women - they treated them very - badly really. Rude and horrible and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Looking back do you think that full time work changed your general attitude to life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Full time work? Do you mean from leaving school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Yes, I think it did because for one thing I made up my mind I wasn't going to spend the whole of my life working. I thought to myself I - I'm going to get some - a job where I'm not working fifty-two week
s a year, going to get where there's some - where there's some - space to live - in between.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Did the family treat you very differently once you were a worker?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 No, I don't think so. Don't remember that they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 I wondered if you suddenly grew up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
No, I don't think I did, I think I was slow growing up really. And - my parents didn't encourage us to grow up. They really kept us children, treated as children, much longer than they do today. And even when I think we were - having jobs it w
as treated more as if we - oh - you know, it's just a - bit of pocket money, it - we weren't a very much - we - we weren't important, our jobs weren't important, it was rather that spirit to begin with. Mind you my - father I think - and mother treated me
 differently when I started teaching, I think they felt that was a real career. They did -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 So that's where your change came?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Thats where my came - my change came.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
You said your parents really considered you grown up when you started teaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 But otherwise it wasn't taken really seriously?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Did starting full time work alter your relationship with your brothers at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Did I want? Oh no, we remained - we've always been the best of friends all our lives. Married - even the married ones.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 When you started work did you spend Sunday any differently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 No, we - we went to church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Just the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Yes. St. Mary's.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 What about Sunday school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 I - I taught by then I should think in the Sunday school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 At that age did you take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Well I - we began to - I was thinking - this week, we be - we must have begun to take an interest in politics about that - because we went to - we always went to hear - people like Jim
 Thomas and Stanley Baldwin's son Oliver who was a Socialist, and broke off his engagement you know because his - he decided that the world wasn't fit for - to put children into. Yes, he did, Oliver Baldwin, and funnily enough, by - one of life's numerous
 coincidences I met the girl he - in Capetown - that he'd broked the engagement. Yes, she'd gone out there after the break, after it was broken, to sort of - for a change.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
You were too young to vote in the first general election weren't you? When women were allowed to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Oh I - I don't think so, no, don't remember anything about voting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Were you interested in any particular party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Well we'd be Conservative.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Why were you a Conservative?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Because - you know, the family had always 
been so, it was that sort of thing, but never the less - we must have - had a lot of - immature - feelings about Socialism because we went to - we always went to hear Oliver Baldwin when he gave a speech. Which he did several times in Bridgford and all ro
und there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Did you have much political discussion in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Well, we must have had a fair amount when ele - when election times came up and that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Did you ever feel under any pressure from anyone to vote for a particular pa
rty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Do you know anyone who did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Pressure to vote for a party? Well - the general public were very much pressured in those days, with you know, vote, vote vote for Henry Bentick and all that sort of thing, and - vans going round and
 - all the - small children being - put on the van and made a fuss of, so that their parents would vote for him.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Did you know of any case where an employer put pressure on an employee or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Oh no - 'cos the only employers I kno
w anything about was the - the Dobsons at the - the cotton mill, and - they certainly didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
You told me earlier on how you spent your spare time, when you started work did you continue to spend your spare time in the same way or did you do different things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Well - the war was on you see. And - my mother - I think must have been a member of the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}St John's{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 ambulance brigade, because she frequently went to the Midland Station to - cope with the troops, and the wounded, and I can remember - rolling 
bandages and all that sort of thing and packing - it was all war, nobody's any idea now what that war was like. Everybody was - doing war things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Did you go out in the evening at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Well I - I can't remember, nothing was happening of course so
 there was nothing to go to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Did you make any new friends at this time, boys or girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
No, I shouldn't think so, only school friends, and who - with whom I'm - I've still kept up several friendships.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Did you have any special friends at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Well my schoolfriends, the friends I'd been friendly with at school I was still friendly with. And of course that - that was when I got engaged. Whom I'd also met at school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Did you bring friends home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Oh yes, the house was always f
ull of youngsters. All the boys had friends and the house was always full of people. And - mother and father were - very often go - at - Easter; and Bank Holidays to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Yorkshire{\*\xmlclose}
, and leave us on our own. We used to have a grand time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Tell me about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
All these - masses of boys and girls used to fill the house, and we used to - have a terrific lot of music and singing and - and - when I think of what dull men some of those boys have made, I think - it seemed quite interesting in those days. And - w
e used to play cards, if it was wet we'd play cards a lot, what we played I don't know but we played cards. And I very well remember - one famous weekend when it was wet, one Easter weekend it was wet and I made hundreds of omelettes and when - mother cam
e back I'd used all the - eggs that were stored in - what did you call it - waterglass. Two great bit pans than were in the - we'd used the lot.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 I should think you were in disgrace weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 No, not really. They took everything - you know, al
l right. And then when - on the East - Easter Sunday night, it suddenly - about midnight it suddenly became beautifully fine, I'd gone to bed, and there was this lovely moon, and somebody came upstairs and said, come on we're going a walk. So I got up and
 
got dressed again and we all went and we walked all round - right - towards Radcliffe and around by Hopepierpoint and I very well remember - one of the chaps was over six foot, and I must - and of course I didn't realize it but I was already a bit deaf, a
n
d he - he said, I love you. I said, what? And I - he got more and more mad at having to repeat this. Oh dear, and I suddenly realized what he'd said, and felt terribly embarrassed. Anyhow, by this time he was in a towering rage - and I walked off with som
e of the others. I still know that chap. I often wonder if he remember that incident.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 You were beginning to go deaf then were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Well you see the ear - ear specialist told me I'd been deaf - I've never had normal hearing. I didn't know, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Did your parents expect to know where you were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Well yes, I think they did more or less.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Did you have to be in by a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Oh I think so, yes, but not too rigid.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 They were fairly easy going really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Yes, but very - they 
knew, where we were and what we were doing all the time, quite definitely. And we shouldn't have dreamt of - say going into a pub or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 That just wouldn't have crossed your mind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 No, no, no we shouldn't have dreamt of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 So it was mostly walking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Oh we did miles of walking and hundreds and hundreds of miles of bi - cycling. We all had bicycles, and - oh - all about - all - all Derbythire and Leicestershire and - Nottinghamshire we - scoured it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Were there any sor
t of theatres or concerts or cinemas, or did everything like that stop during the war?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
I remember taking my youngest brother to see - the - Exploits of Elaine. A serial at the cinema. I took him in one wet - wet day, of course he was trilled and wan
ted to go to see what happened next but - always ended with a - a sword or a spear or something just popping - chopping her head off or something, or she was falling down a waterfall and we had to go the next week. But apart from that, I don't remember us
 going. But we must have gone occasionally. We went to a skating rink.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 During the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Well it must have been during the war because after that we were - sort of too grown up to do these things in a way. We went to a skating rink - it was somewhe
re in the town, I think where the covered market now is. And - later on we went to tea dances at the Palais de Dance, Saturday afternoon, very nice. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 You obviously enjoyed this time of life very much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 We - we really had a very nice - happy c
hildhood, we hadn't much money - but we enjoyed our - we were very happy. Pop always used to say - that the first sixteen years of his married life were the happiest years of his life. Yes, in spite of everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 When you were all young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Yes, b
ut of course you see with the war, with having to shut his business and go to the war we lost all his - that he'd built up. And he never really was quite the same again, he - it had killed his early enthusiasm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 You did say your mother had some help with the house didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Yes, she did until the war of course. And then apart from the fact that there wasn't anyone to do it, of course they were all on munitions - she wouldn't have felt she could have afforded it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 You had Mrs Moffatt seventeen years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Yes, I can't remember whether it was fifteen or seventeen, but somewhere about that. All the time we were young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Did anyone help after that? You I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Yes, I - I - I did a terrific lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 If your mother was ill or confined to bed how did she manage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Oh - oh she - she loved being - having a baby because - she always stayed in her room for a month, they did in those days, and - nurse Taylor always came, she came for all of us. And stayed a month or so, and - mother used
 to say it was the only real rest she had.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Do you remember any of this yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
I remem - I remember when Harry was born and the nurse came in the early hours of the morning and said to me, come and see your new little brother. I said, not another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Did your parents have any relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 No, see they were all in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Yorkshire
{\*\xmlclose}, both - on both sides, but they were always coming and going.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 You did go and stay with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Kept in touch, oh yes, I went to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
Yorkshire{\*\xmlclose} a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Did your parents have friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Oh yes, they had a lot of friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Where did they see them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Well, they belonged to the Yorkshire Society. And - they were always coming and going and - visiting each other and all that sort of thing, Christmas parties, birthday parties, with all the kids and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Did they share the same friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Oh yes, definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Did your mother have any friends of her own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 No, I don't think you would - you could say she had any of her own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Did your father have any of his own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Well of course he had a lot of business friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Where would he have seen them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Well - I don't know, during - business - he didn't - I don't think he belonged to a club, apart from - the only club they belo
nged to was the Yorkshire one, and later my mother belonged to the Dickens Society. That was the only thing she did on her own. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Friends were often invited to the house from what you say?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Well there always seemed to be a lot, some of them coming and going.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Would your parents friends be offered anything to eat or drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Would the parents friends what? Oh yes, you know what Yorkshire people are, you can't appear before you have to eat and drink. Oh very - good - great difference betw
een the - meals and the food and drink - that we had in Yorkshire and those we had when we visited Nottingham people. So much so that we - even children used to notice it. I remember the famous day when we were - children were taken to tea somewhere and w
hen we'd finished, Noel, who was always an infant terrible said thank you very much, I'll go home and have me proper tea now. The poor woman's never forgotten it. Oh, you know, it was thin bread and butter and tiny little sandwiches.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Would you say the 
friends invited to your home were both your parents friends rather than one or the other's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Oh yes, both.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Did friends call in casually without an invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Did what? I couldn't definitely say but I should say they did occasionally, if they did they would be - all right, it wouldn't matter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Did neighbours ever pop in without an invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Yes, occasionally. Mother was fairly friendly with neighbours. But she wasn't the sort of woman who would go - to them. They came to her, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Were often told in those days they made their own amusements, what do you think your parents did when they got together with their friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Well I don't know what they'd do really apart from - eating drinking and talking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Music?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 The
y - I don't think - you see - mother's father - had been a - a very - strict - highly religious man, and before he died at sea and before he died he made - the three girls promise they would never play cards and never dance.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Not even dance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Neve
r go to a dance. Since mother's been dead I've found all the letter he wrote from sea to them and they're beautiful. Yes, wonderful letters. And of course they both promised and they all three kept - they all three kept that promise and - it wasn't until 
- oh I should think mother would be - fifty or something like that before she played a game of cards.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Did he make them promise not to drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Well the - every - no - none of them drink in that circle. I don't think -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 It wasn't mentioned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
It - no, it - nobody would drink, they were - grandfather Martin and grandmother Smales were both - super religious. I think - grandfather Smales - he crept over the line and - drank a - quite a large fortune away. Yes. But not grandpa Martin.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Many
 people divide society into different social classes or groups, in that time before 1919 did you think of some people belonging to one and some to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Oh yes, I think quite definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 You thought about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Yes. Oh yes, I think there 
were quite definitely - three - distinct set - classes in that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Can you tell me about them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Well there were the working class, who were definitely - they didn't - didn't - in a way they were some - a lot of them were quite proud of being wor
king class, didn't want to be anything else. And - then at the top were the - you know, people like the Portlands and the Bentincks and all that lot who you thought of as being very superior in those days and different specie altogether. And then all the 
ones in the middle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 You actually thought about this at that age?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
I think it's looking back - more - mostly, it's difficult to sort it out. But with - as far as the working class concerned of course - there must have been terrible poverty because 
the homes - if you went into a home there'd be no carpets or table cloths, anything like that. It would be clean, very clean. And - the people were all I'm sure much more contented and happy than they are today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 You feel this do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Yes. Even t
hose who were very poor. But they - if you - the table - would be a deal table, there'd be nothing on it, bare, no cloth of any sort. And there'd be no carpets anywhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
What sort of people would you have thought of as belonging to the working class then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Well - people who'd - did sort of odd labouring - jobs or worked in - rough clothes and that sort of thing. There was a lot of poverty in that - period.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 What class would you say you belonged to then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Oh I should say we belonged to the middle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 What were the other sort of people who belonged to the middle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
You know, I'm thinking of all the people really who went to the same schools and that sort of thing, and their parents would be - you know, clerks and - all that sort of - job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 What sort of people would belong to this lot you called very superior?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Well they'd be what today are known as County people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another sort?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 In a vague way I should say yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Can you tell me anything about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Except of course - but - we - with my people being - parents being so - what today people would call goody-goody you were - always had to be very polite and - good mannered to ev
eryone. And in fact - my father did a lot of - he - he - if anybody came to him and asked him for five bob - a down and out chap, he would always give it. Although he couldn't really afford it half - most of the time, but he did. He never refused a - help
.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 I'm sure nothing of that sort ever happened 'cos I'd have remembered it.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Could you tell me again who you had to call sir or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Well I think the - the church people, not the curates perhaps but the others - we nearly always had a Bishop at St Mary's in those days. Bishop Talbot and Bishop Baines. And all those people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Do you remember anyone showing respect to your parents in these ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Well - yes, I should think some of the working - men, probably those that came for help wanted something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 What did your Mrs Moffat call your mother?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Can't remember do you know. Ma'am I should think. We always had to call her mother, we }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15033757\charrsid11885113 weren\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113  allowed - to call her any middle name. And father, although as we - later on we - I started calling him pop and to the end of his life I called him pop. But that was later.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Not when you were little?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Do you remember when you changed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 When I got to the cheeky age I should think, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 He probably liked it really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Yes he did, he did like it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 You never changed for your mother though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 No. Never changed with mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
In the district where you lived who were considered the most important people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Oh dear, I don't know. I can't remember any
body being outstandingly important.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
You just talk about the Portlands etc. because you've heard of them since, they didn't impinge then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Well - they were always very - around very much at - election time. And - charity things and the - and - eve
rything to do with - charity bazaars and fetes and - fairs in the market place, the Duchess was always there, everybody knew the Duchess, and she knew everybody. Or gave you the impression she knew you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Did you come in contact with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Yes, be
cause we had a patriotic fair in the market. Which was wonderful. And - with hundreds of stalls and everyone of the stalls was - in charge of a - of - some important person. All these mysterious important people, and - I think it was organised by the Duch
ess. But as far as Nottingham was concerned - when the Duchess was young she was very much part of {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Nottingham{\*\xmlclose}. Yes, very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Why were these people considered important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Well I think be - because she did so much for everything and everybody, she
 worked so hard for everything and everybody. She took an interest in everything and everybody. It must have been a very outstanding woman.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 She was a very special person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Yes. You know that - for the whole of her life - Queen - Princess - Queen
 Mary - no, the Duke of Windsor's mother - gave orders that whenever she was leaving London the - Station Master at St Pancras was to personally see her off. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 What about the shopkeepers, who did they associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Oh we all associated with - more or less everybody. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 What about the clergy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Well - I think the clergy did too. We all - we - seemed to have - I don't know whether it was because of the - we seemed to have a terrific lot to do with the - all the - curates and parsons of St Mary's all our lives.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 What about teachers, who did they associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Schoolteachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Until - yes, until I went to - Mandella the only one I ever remember was Miss Claggert, at the little church school, and - at Mandella - we were all very friendly with the - staff, but they were very much up there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 I don't suppose you know much about farmers do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 No, not - very much really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 What about employers, who did they associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Well - I - I - apart fr
om - all their own crowd, I think that was about all. People worked very long hours in those days. And they - there wasn't a lot of time for - spare time activities.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 What sort of people would you say went to the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Well I should say everybo
dy. A very - big section. I shouldn't imagine the - the - sort - what I call the working class ones went. But it was really the strata above that. And then going up, right up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 What sort of people went to the chapel?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Oh I don't know, I never went to the chapel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Do you think there was any feeling between the church and chapel, did you come across anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Well I don't think they were friendly. You know, they each thought they were superior, I think there was a lot of that spirit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Where you lived did all the people in the working class have the same standard of living as each other or do you think there were different groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Oh no, a terrific variety. Whether that was caused because of bad management and good management I don't know, but there was - there were a lot of stratas, and of course drink was a great problem in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Did you come across families in different groups you could tell us about, when you were visiting with your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Yes, I can 
remember this family where I - for some reason used to go and see this bare table and - and the children standing round instead of sitting for their meals. And - always spotlessly clean. And the - mother - and I - to my - great irritation - used to say, w
a
ste not want not, for you may live to - and - something like that, you know, want a little crumb or something. Oh she always used to recite this, it irritated me to death. And the miners, I used to go to the miners at - Hucknall with my father who did qui
t
e a lot of business with them. And - their homes were always potless, and they - in spite of all the talk there is today they never gave me the impression of being poverty stricken. No. Definitely not. I used to go because I used to love to see the furnac
e
s blazing. And I'd go with father while he was doing business I'd - one of the - children would - take me to see the furnaces again and that sort of thing. And - the miners would come home - and - and they'd have - they had thick flannel shirts which were
 
- today would cost ten pounds at least, and they'd - the wife would pour - water into the - hot water into a great big zinc bath, in the scullery. Then they'd get into it and get bathed. But they were such a happy - such a nice lot of people. No bad langu
age. At least not - I - I never heard any. And - they always seemed happy, contented.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Do you think one group in the working class thought itself superior to the rest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Well only - they did but only in a minor sort of way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Were some families thought of as rough and others as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Oh I think so, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Do you remember a distinction of this kind between craftsmen and labourers?

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Well - yes, I think craftsmen - are - there were a lot of good craftsmen in those days and there
 were very proud of being good craftsman, and - and rather - rather sort of off people - young boys who - or anybody like that who wouldn't become a good craftsman. Do shoddy work, they were very much against that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Did both your parents have the same 
attitude as each other to people in different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Oh I think so, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to a particular social class or group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 I shouldn't think she ever thought much about it. No, I don't think so.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 What about your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Oh no, he definitely wouldn't, he was very much - hale fellow, well met, with everybody was his equal. He treated everybody equally, high or low.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 So he didn't think about it much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 You told me last time about this family who moved up from Narrow Marsh?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Oh yes, in - in the Cape.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Can you tell me anything like that that you knew yourself in this country? Or do you think you had to go abroad in order to move from one class to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Yes, I should think that would be the case really. While I was in 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}South Africa{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 - I should think on the whole I moved with a - at any rate definitely a more wealthy class than I'd ever moved with before. But - as I - never would take a - a permanent job, I - I o
nly took temporary jobs, I - moved about a terrific lot, and quite often I'd meet people at the - Overseas Club and they'd say, you'd get talking to them over dinner in the evening, and they'd say, oh come home with me for a few weeks tomorrow, and I'd go
. So I went to all sorts of different - I - I got awfully friendly with a Doctor Maraget Gray while I was - at one period. She was Mrs Best really but she refused to use her married name ever. And she and I started a library - in - right up near the 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Kalahari Desert{\*\xmlclose}, a very - I went and stayed with them, and we - we started a - a really very good library, we got - three enormous crates of books sent out from London.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 This is after 1918 though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Yes. And I often wonder if it's still going.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Do you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Oh yes. Oh I think people very much - in those days - felt pleasure if they met anyone that they - thought of as - being a real gentleman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Why do you think somebody would be described as a real gentleman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Well I think it was largely a - a - a matter of manners and grooming.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 What about a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Oh - a - real ladies had to be - very - they were - very sort of - starchy and - well seemed so to children. Demanded a terrifically high standard of everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Do you remember seeing a policeman around where you lived as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Oh yes, a police - pop, owing to his business was what he used to call himself, well known to the police. Oh and all the police - knew we children. And Martin got lost they - quickly - rally round and found her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 What did you think of the police?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Oh - of course we were all friendly because - they were always in and out.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 How did you think he treated the people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Treated the peo
ple? Well it depended on the people. If they were rough drunks or something like that they were quite ruthless with them. Or if there were any - fighting which you sometimes saw in those days, they would - go and take them by the scruff of their neck and 
throw them - down and then take them all away, bustle them away quickly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Was your home rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Yes, it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Did you see anything of your landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Shouldn't think so, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 So you can't say how you felt about him as a landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
No, but - pop was such a friendly man that I expect he was quite friendly with us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Do you remember feeling your parents had a struggle to make ends meet?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Well definitely did - after - for a year or two after the war. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 What did you think about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Oh - I worried about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Was your father ever ill or out of work before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
No. Neither mother nor father were ever ill. I can't remember - any of them ever being ill, apart from when mother had the baby.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Did you or 
did you ever know anyone ever get help from the Guardians or the Parish or any charity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
Not personally I don't think. Of course Noel became - Secretary to the - one of the alms house charities, through his job, he was trained as a solicitor. And we used to hear a - him talk a lot about them, but I didn't really know anybody personally.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 
About rough music, you said you'd never come across this way of showing disapproval?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 No. No, the only disapproval I've any recollection of is if somebody sud
denly - being sort of - stopping - you stopped seeing them and - you - they sort of more or less disappeared.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4222835 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Can you remember any special instance of this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid404251 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113 Well - only very }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15033757\charrsid11885113 dimly}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7875416\charrsid11885113  there was a - a friends - some friend of - my aunt's - who I thin
